{"root":{"data":{"id":"d8dhcqf0lmw0","created":1741700653649,"text":"感兴趣的科学学科"},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dhcyc5htc0","created":1741700670890,"text":"Describe a science subject that you are interested in\nYou should say:\nWhat it is\nWhere you got to know it How you have learned it\nAnd explain why you are interested in it"},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dhdii8sg80","created":1741700714794,"text":"One science subject\n\n\nthat I am deeply interested in is environmental science.\n\n\nI first became fascinated by it during high school. When I took an introductory course in science.\n\n\nWe studied topics like climate change,\n\n\nbiodiversity and the impact of human activities on the environment.\n\n\nIt was eye opening to learn about the delicate balance in nature,\n\n\nandhow everything is interconnected.\n\n\nSince then,\n\n\ni've continued to explore environmental science through various means.\n\n\nI read books and research articles.\n\n\nandI follow several environmental science pod casts\n\n\nand documentaries to stay updated on the latest developments.\n\n\nAdditionally,\n\n\ni've taken a few online courses to deepen my knowledge,\n\n\nespecially about sustainability and renewable energy.\n\n\nWhat really draws me to environmental science is its relevance to today's world\n\n\nwith the growing concerns about climate change,\n\n\npollution and resource depletion,\n\n\nunderstanding these issues has become more important than ever.\n\n\nI feel that this subject gives me the tools to not only understand the problems,\n\n\nbut also think about potential solutions.\n\n\nI'm especially interested in how science can help create more sustainable practices,\n\n\nwhether it's in agriculture,\n\n\nenergy production or urban planning.\n\n\nThe idea of contributing to a healthier planet is both inspiring and motivating to me,\n\n\nwhich is why I continue to learn and stay engaged with this field."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"id":"d8dhs8uhplk0","created":1741701869229,"text":"Why do some children not like learning science at school?","layout_mind_offset":{"x":-55.00000411272026,"y":-17.999999731778985}},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dht62xtag0","created":1741701941574,"text":"Some children may not enjoy learning science because it can be perceived as difficult or abstract,\n\n\nespecially when concepts like physics or chemistry seem unrelated to their daily lives.\n\n\nAdditionally, if the subject is taught in a monotonous theoretical manner without hands on activities,\n\n\nstudents might lose interest. Moreover, the pressure of exams and a lack of encouragement from teachers\n\n\nor parents can further discourage children, making them view science as a subject to memorize rather than explore creatively.","layout_left_offset":{"x":-1188.999992564321,"y":138.99999792873848}},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"id":"d8diznwobs00","created":1741705271672,"text":"Is it important to study science at school?"},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dizxiipy80","created":1741705292584,"text":"Yes. Studying science at school is crucial as it helps develop critical thinking,\n\n\nproblem solving and analytical skills, which are essential in today's world.\n\n\nScience encourages curiosity and a deeper understanding of how the world works,\n\n\nfostering innovation and technological advancement.\n\n\nMoreover, it prepares students for a wide range of careers from health care to engineering. In addition,\n\n\nscientific literacy is vital for informed decision making in daily life,\n\n\nparticularly when addressing global challenges like climate change and public health.","layout_left_offset":{"x":-759.9999895393851,"y":-25.99999961256981}},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"id":"d8dj02dwhrs0","created":1741705303189,"text":"Which science subject is the most important for children to learn?"},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dj09hko800","created":1741705318648,"text":"It's difficult to pinpoint just one science subject as the most important as each offers unique benefits. However,\n\n\nI believe that biology is particularly essential. As it helps children understand the basics of life,\n\n\nhealth, and the environment with growing concerns over global health and ecological issues.\n\n\nKnowledge of biology is increasingly relevant that said subjects like physics and chemistry are also vital\n\n\nas they provide the foundation for technological and scientific advancements in our modern world.","layout_left_offset":{"x":-722.9999892264607,"y":49.99999925494194}},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"id":"d8dj0en77kg0","created":1741705329872,"text":"Should people continue to study science after graduating from school?","layout_mind_offset":{"x":-16,"y":0}},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dj0hbop8g0","created":1741705335706,"text":"Yes. People should continue studying science after graduating from school.\n\n\nAs it promotes lifelong learning and keeps individuals informed about the latest advancements. Science is constantly evolving,\n\n\nand staying updated is crucial for adapting to new technologies and global challenges.\n\n\nMoreover, pursuing further studies in science can lead to career opportunities in various fields,\n\n\nsuch as medicine, research and environmental sustainability.\n\n\nOverall, ongoing education in science fosters critical thinking,\n\n\nproblem solving skills and innovation, which benefit both individuals and society.","layout_left_offset":{"x":-965.9999993741512,"y":221.99999669194221}},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"id":"d8dj1awpxz40","created":1741705400105,"text":"How do you get to know about scientific news?"},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dj1mqzzog0","created":1741705425880,"text":"I typically get to know about scientific news through a variety of sources. I follow reputable science websites,\n\n\nsuch as scientific American and nature to stay informed about the latest discoveries. Social media platforms,\n\n\nespecially Twitter, are also useful for real time updates and discussions among experts. Additionally,\n\n\nI watch documentaries and listen to podcasts that cover scientific topics.\n\n\nThese methods help me stay current and gain a broader understanding of emerging trends\n\n\nand breakthroughs in the scientific world.","layout_left_offset":{"x":-813.9999972581863,"y":187.9999971985817}},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"id":"d8dj1s9n1vs0","created":1741705437891,"text":"Should scientists explain the research process to the public?"},"children":[{"data":{"id":"d8dj20cepi00","created":1741705455473,"text":"Yes, scientists should explain the research process to the public as it promotes transparency and fosters trust.\n\n\nWhen the public understands how research is conducted, including methods and ethical considerations,\n\n\nthey are more likely to support scientific initiatives.\n\n\nAdditionally,\n\n\nexplaining complex research in accessible terms can inspire interest and encourage future generations to pursue science.\n\n\nThis open communication also helps bridge the gap between scientific communities and the public,\n\n\nmaking science more relevant and accessible to everyone."},"children":[]}]}]},"template":"default","theme":"fresh-blue","version":"1.4.43"}